Plant.create(name: "delta maidenhair fern", 
img_url:"https://mulhalls.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/MaidenhairFern-Post-1.jpg", 
info: "Care Information
Light
Will take quite a low light spot, not the best for windowsills.

Temperature
Likes it quite warm but away from radiators etc.

Water
Keep it well watered all through late spring to early autumn making sure it does not dry out. Over winter cut back a little on water.

Feeding
Feed every 4-6 weeks over the summer best to double the dilution rate (add more water) as they really do not like too much feed. Do not feed over the winter.

Tip
Mist when you can as low humidity can cause leaf browning.")

Plant.create(name: "Zebra Basket Vine", 
img_url:"http://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0215/9765/1008/products/zebravine_10HBc_43ce8c49-9d85-4c38-ae24-8c08a438c3ce_1200x1200.jpg?v=1566995362", 
info: "Care Information
Lighting
Does like bright, indirect sunlight but can tolerate some direct sunlight. Hang it near an East or West facing window.

Temperature
Normal room temprature will be fine for this plant. 

Water
Water this plant moderately, not letting it sit in water. It does not seem to mind a bit of time dry but prefers the compost on the moist side through the summer.

Feeding
Feed every other month during growing period (Spring-Autumn)

Tip
Because this plant is oringinally from the tropics it likes high humidity if possible. ")

Plant.create(name: " 'Mona Lisa' Lipstick plant", 
img_url:"http://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0074/0022/6905/products/0.6_afa1a8ef-cb69-4ddb-8b56-88f997d13bb7.PNG?v=1571719634", 
info: "Care Information
Lighting
A bright spot away from direct light is best but if kept on the dry side will take lower light levels.

Temperature
Not too fussy but keep above 10 celcius

Water
Water sparingly over winter and more over spring-summer. Dunking the pot into water is the easiest way. Wait for the compost to dty slightly before watering.

Feeding
A balanced feed every three weeks or so over the summer

Tip
Tomato food will increase the number of flowers (use when you can see the first flower buds)")

Plant.create(name: "String of Hearts", 
img_url:"https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img,w_400/https://roomforinspo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/String-of-hearts-Plantenasiel-Voorburg.jpeg", 
info: "Care Information
Lighting
The plant does like a bright spot but not direct sunlight. It can also do well in low light levels as well. 

Temperature
Normal room temprature will be fine for this plant. (around 15°C)

Water
Should only be watered when completely dry and should never be stood in water.

Feeding
Feed during growing season which is spring to mid summer. 

Tip
A south facing window would be a good setting for this plant as needs the warmth but only as long as there isn't direct light on it. ")

Plant.create(name: "Grape Ivy", 
img_url:"https://i5.walmartimages.com/asr/aa224dbc-b491-4aae-91a8-5ee381f52943_1.178cba12b414a44ee9ccee95c03b4c12.jpeg", 
info: "Care Information
Lighting
Direct sunlight will scorch the leaves but apart from this it will grow happily in bright light to mid shade. It will get a little lanky in a really dark spot, just pinch out the ends of the vine.

Temperature
Normal indoor tempratures are fine, over 30 celcius for too long can cause problems.

Water
Really important to let it dry out inbetween watering. Then make sure the roots get a drink (rather than it running down the side of the dry compost!)

Feeding
Half strength liquid feed onec every 5-8 weeks over the spring/summer seasons.

Tip
The leaves should be a dark green if they are light then it needs a feed.")

Plant.create(name: "Hare's Foot Fern", 
img_url:"https://s7d1.scene7.com/is/image/terrain/56997398_000_a?$zoom2$", 
info: "Care Information
Lighting
Light shade.

Temperature
Average warmth.

Water
Water well in the growing season but do not allow the compost to become waterlogged.

Feeding
A liquid feed every month or so.

Tip
Mist the hanging rhizomes occasionally and don't overfeed.")

Plant.create(name: "String of nickels", 
img_url:"https://i.pinimg.com/originals/23/2f/90/232f90eaa67ef4d297e34ca581ecda4d.jpg", 
info: "Care Information
Lighting
Prefers filtered sun. Direct sunlight can be tolerated for short periods of time.

Temperature
Standard room temperature 

Water
Water regularly during the growing season. It likes to dry out a bit in between watering but try not let it dry out completely. Ideally mist daily to retain moisture. 

Feeding
No need to fertize but repot plants annually to replace nutrients. You can feed with liquid houseplant food during the growing season if desired. 

Tip
If your plant is subjected to direct sunlight, be sure to water it well. 

Trim stems to shape the plant as desired. Save cuttings to grow new plants.

When repotting, you can use a variety of well draining potting mixes, such as a good orchid mix.")

Plant.create(name: "Fishbone cactus", 
img_url:"https://i.pinimg.com/originals/d0/4d/77/d04d77d77dac4eadb8b8e449b7d27c4f.jpg", 
info: "Care Information
Lighting
Best out of the hottest full sun, a well lit bright spot is best.

Temperature
Will go down to around 8 celcius if dry over the winter but best above 10.

Water
Lots over Spring - Early autumn and then cut right back. Always let it dry out inbetween waterings.

Feeding
A weak cactus feed over the growing season every two weeks or so.

Tip
In late Summer/Early autumn make sure its getting a bit of full sun as this will help it to produce the stunning flowers.")

Plant.create(name: "Marble Queen", 
img_url:"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0147/6362/2500/products/IMG_20200709_190025_2048x.jpg?v=1594351722", 
info: "Care Information
Site
It will cope just fine in a darker spot, but if you really want the variegations to shine through it needs a spot with bright indirect sunlight

Temperature
It likes it warm, but will tolerate temperatures down to about 13°C

Water
Water once the compost is dry and allow to remain dry before watering during winter

Feeding
A weak house plant food once or twice a month during summer to stimulate growth

Tip
Super easy to propagate. Just remove one of the stems with nodes, place in compost and you're away!")

Plant.create(name: "Golden Pothos", 
img_url:"https://www.picclickimg.com/d/l400/pict/233518864348_/Golden-Pothos-Scindapsus-Epipremnum-Scandens-NEON.jpg", 
info: "Care Information
Site
Bright but not direct sunglight. Do not go too shady, or the yellows will turn to green. 

Temperature
Make sure not to let it get too cold, around 13°C and above is required. 

Water
Will grow quickly in spring and summer with regular lots of soaking. Be sure to allow the compost to dry out between watering though and only water about once a month during winter. It loves a mist, so spray with fine water as often as you like!

Feeding
Benefits from a liquid feed once a month. 

Tip
Pinch out the growing end tips of the plant and it will grow into an attractive bush shape. ")

Plant.create(name: "Nerve Plant", 
img_url:"http://theplantsgarden.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/FittoniaNerve-Plant1.jpg", 
info: "Care Information
Site
A sunny spot without direct sunlight will allow the colours to come out at their brightest. A terrarium is perfect.

Temperature
Warm and humid to allow maximum growth and plant health.

Water
The soil should be moist but well drained. Do not allow to dry out. 

Feeding
Once a month during the growing season.

Tip
As with many vibrant plants, the colouration of the leaves depends on the amount of light it gets. The perfect balance of brightness without direct sunlight will bring out the striking reds and whites in all their glory.")

Plant.create(name: "Wax Flower", 
img_url:"https://st.hzcdn.com/fimgs/8692219a04ced34d_0656-w500-h388-b0-p0--.jpg", 
info: "Care Information
Site
Needs more light than the non variegated form but best out of very hot summer sun. Likes a bit ow humidity so away from radiators is best.

Temperature
Wont mind getting a little chilly as long as its feet are in dry compost. But keep it away from those cold winter draughts.

Water
Best to leave it alone if damp at all. Does not mind drying out for a while.

Feeding
Give it very regular feeds in Spring and summer (every two weeks or so) with a liquid feed and will grow and grow.

Tip
Dont pot it up into a big pot the roots like drying out. ")

Plant.create(name: "Forest Cactus", 
img_url:"https://i.pinimg.com/originals/c9/a9/86/c9a986e4f64a3b2502e4c40830d1c56c.jpg", 
info: "Care Information
Site
A versatile cactus, it will do well anywhere out of direct sunlight

Temperature
It will do best kept above 15°C

Water
Just leave it alone in the winter, and during summer only water when the compost is totally, totally bone dry. When that time comes, soak it completely.

Feeding
A cactus food once a month during summer.

Tip
Avoid humid rooms such as bathrooms and kitchens, and ensure the pot has plenty of drainage.")

Plant.create(name: "Prayer Plant", 
img_url:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTYlXV1hvWuYLwP8cFmhwsD99pZ5kKkrw7mAsqV1SUC8MwThLjYShWthnhr2fYtgu-w9XI&usqp=CAU", 
info: "Care Information
Site
Light to dark shade in summer. Brighter in winter but keep out of direct sun, this will dull the colour of the leaves, and could be fatal!

Temperature
Keep warm minimum of 16°C / 60°F.

Water
Keep well watered in summer, Maranta loves high humidity mist when you can and keep the compost moist in the summer. Brown tips show that the humidity is too low.

Feeding
Feed with a very weak solution when you water. Don't give it a strong feed every now and then.

Tip
Do not re-pot too often and use a peat based compost.")

Plant.create(name: "Herringbone Plant", 
img_url:"https://media.karousell.com/media/photos/products/2017/07/17/potted_maranta_leuconeura_erythroneura_prayer_plant_herringbone_plant_1500272950_051f04080", 
info: "Care Information
Site
Light shade in summer. Brighter in winter but keep out of direct sun, this will dull the colour of the leaves, and could be fatal!

Temperature
Keep warm minimum of 16°C / 60°F.

Water
Keep well watered in summer, Maranta loves high humidity mist when you can and keep the compost moist in the summer. Brown tips show that the humidity is too low.

Feeding
Feed with a very weak solution when you water. Don't give it a strong feed every now and then.

Tip
Do not repot too often and use a peat based compost.")

Plant.create(name: "Kangaroo Fern", 
img_url:"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/proxy/JFgOpCjy4yObHckr21F7uQ2vSNNUc2paI9NR5AevoNcxaw8dVLXLUvyRaKFu-a9D3Sna9VRL5NUCRPe6j5Z5VnF3IfRNKW6QuZtNHige7T67YCKDAPrNO0aPP0aptPGoJfGPNa0UckZTnKI", 
info: "Care Information
Site
Medium light. Keep it out of direct sun, it will tolerate lower light levels as well.

Temperature
It does not like to get too cold, round about 20 celcius is great.

Water
Requires average water regularly, but do not overwater.

 

Feeding
Ferns do not require much feed. A balanced plant food at 1/2 the recommended strength, once a month

Do not fertilize in the winter. ")

Plant.create(name: "Neoregelia 'Fireball'", 
img_url:"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0022/4473/9133/products/neoregelia-fireball-bromeliads-bromeliad-paradise_600x.jpg?v=1542292420", 
info: "Care Information
Site
Bright indirect light.

Temperature
Average warmth after flowering and hates cold or dry air, keep the humidity up.

Water
After flowering keep the well at the centre of the plant topped up over the growing season. In winter keep on the dry side and do not water into the 'well'. Keep humidity up by misting.

Feeding
A very weak liquid feed every month or so over the growing season.

Tip
A tip to get it to reflower is to let the water dry in the centre of the plant then place it in a plastic bag with a ripe apple for a week or so. The apple gives off ethylene gas which stimulates f")

Plant.create(name: "Dark Green Beetle Radiator Plant", 
img_url:"data:image/jpeg;base64,", 
info: "Care Information
Site
Will tolerate a wide range of light levels, but will do best in the shade. It can also grow under flourescent lights, meaning it's perfect for windowless rooms. Don't expect huge amounts of growth though.

Temperature
Do not let it drop below 13 Celcius.

Water
It does not like to become waterlogged at all, so water sparingly.

Feeding
A liquid feed once or twice a month during spring and summer and not during winter or early autumn.

Tip
If you place the trailing stems over a pot of new compost, it will form new roots and start re-developing.")

Plant.create(name: "String of Coins", 
img_url:"https://candidegardening.com/img/83b75ac7-48a1-4528-95e0-0b9424138856/cropped/600x480", 
info: "Care Information
Site
A medium-shade spot, with diffused sunlight. No direct light. 

Temperature
A warm spot with moderate humidity.

Water
Water once a week during the hottest months and about once or twice a month in colder seasons. Do not allow the compost to dry out completely or sit in water. Ensure adequate drainage.

Feeding
Once every second watering during the growing months, but not at all during the winter.

Tip
Position the growing vines over a fresh, empty pot of compost and they will form new roots.")

Plant.create(name: "Trailing Jade Plant", 
img_url:"https://heyplants.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/il_fullxfull.2513918951_5ys8-scaled.jpg", 
info: "Care Information
Site
Bright shade without direct sunlight, except non-intense morning or evening sun. Midday sun may risk scorching the leaves. 

Temperature
This plant naturally grows in hot climates and is sensitive to sudden drops in temperature. If taking cuttings from the plant to propagate, try to provide temperatures of 20C with bright light to the cuttings when they are in soil. 

Water
Be careful not to overwater. Allow the soil to dry completely then water it thoroughly. Water very sparingly in winter. During summer, mist the leaves.

Feeding
During spring, use a diluted fertilizer once every two weeks. Drop to once a month during summer months, and drop feeding completely during autumn and winter. 

Tip
Can easily be cut back to maintain shape. These cuttings can be used to propagate new plants. ")

Plant.create(name: "Velvet Heart", 
img_url:"https://smartgardenguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/philodendron-varieties-philodendron-hederaceum.jpg", 
info: "Care Information
Site
Highly adaptable, this plant will cope in a wide range of light levels. If you however want to maximise the colouration of the leaves, place in a bright spot out of direct sunlight. East or West facing windows are usually best.

Temperature
Average warmth. Do not expose to sustained temperatures of 13 Celcius or less.

Water
Will do best in damp, well drained and aerated soil. Allow to dry out slightly before totally soaking.

Feeding
Benefits from feeding in the growing season with a well-diluted solution about twice a month.

Tip
The leaves will never grow more than about 7cm across, so no matter how bushy or tall it gets, it will always maintain the same appearance. ")

Plant.create(name: "Sweetheart Plant", 
img_url:"https://candidegardening.com/img/e1a398fa-9aac-4746-952b-1fa35b51b014/cropped/616x493", 
info: "Care Information
Site
Anywhere shady. Breathes life into isolated corners and dark shelves where it loves trailing off. 

Temperature
Can cope with drafts and chills unlike many other tropical plants, but will thrive best in a warmer environment. 

Water
Water regularly in the summer months, allowing the compost to dry out in between. Water sparingly during winter. 

Feeding
Very unfussy. You can feed it once a month in the summer, and once every two months during the rest of the year, but use the concentration at half the recommended strength. 

Tip
One of the easiest plants to propagate! The offshoots are so numerous that one plant can produce hundreds of cuttings!")

Plant.create(name: "Philodendron Cobra", 
img_url:"https://i.etsystatic.com/15627095/r/il/78fe16/2723214573/il_300x300.2723214573_gqwy.jpg", 
info: "Care Information
Site
Bright indirect light without any direct sunshine except in the early morning or late evening

Temperature
A warmer environment, be sure not to let it drop below 14°C 

Water
Water regularly and soak the compost completely but make sure the pot has lots of drainage. The roots hate sitting in water. Allow to dry out slightly before watering again.

Feeding
 A weak liquid plant feed during summer will bring out the best of this plants brilliant colours

Tip
We would advise taking cuttings from this plant and propagating it! They will not be available commercially for long! ")

Plant.create(name: "Blue Star Fern", 
img_url:"http://theplantsgarden.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Phlebodium-Aureum1.jpg", 
info: "Care Information
Site
Anywhere, but loves darker areas with dappled spots of indirect light. Grows brilliantly in a bathroom.

Temperature
Naturally found in warm areas, but will handle the cold better than a lot of plants. Be careful of allowing a freshly watered plant to be exposed to cold to avoid root rot. 

Water
Will benefit from heavy watering, and it really enjoys regular misting as well. Water sparingly during colder months. Do not allow the soil to dry out. 

Feeding
As it's such an unfussy plant, there's little need to feed it. Use a heavily diluted feed once or twice during the summer months and avoid altogether during winter. 

Tip
An absolute trooper. The plant's epiphytic habit and hardy rhizomes allow it to flourish in some unforgiving environments in the wild, and it is hugely versatile as a result. ")

Plant.create(name: "Gray Artillery Plant", 
img_url:"https://smartgardenguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/pilea-glauca-care-7.jpg", 
info: "Care Information
Site
A nice bright spot away from direct sun

Temperature
A warmer than average houseplant. Will thrive if kept at and above 20°C but can tolerate it down to about 15°C

Water
Keep the soil moist in summer (but not waterlogged) and allow to dry out in winter

Feeding
Feed it ocassionally during summer

Tip
Absolutely adores being misted once or more a week. Especially in hot weather.")

Plant.create(name: "Staghorn fern", 
img_url:"https://i0.wp.com/plantingman.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Staghorn-Fern-Platycerium-bifurcatum.jpg?fit=800%2C800&ssl=1", 
info: "Care Information
Site
Shady to light shade.

Temperature
Keep warm 60°F / 70°F.

Water
Keep well watered in summer and infrequently in winter. Needs pretty high humidity so do not place near to any heating.

Feeding
A very weak liquid feed every month or so.

Tip
Water by immersing into a bowl of tepid water.")

Plant.create(name: "Mistletoe cacti",
img_url:"https://smartgardenguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/rhipsalis-care-mistletoe-cactus-10-1-783x528.jpg", 
info: "Care Information
Site
Bright indirect light. Morning or evening sun is okay, no midday sun.

Temperature
Best if kept above 15°C

Water
Water copiously throughout summer, but allow to dry in between waterings; and water a little over winter.

Feeding
Once every 4 weeks through summer with a weak cactus fertiliser.

Tip
Never ever let it sit in water and usea free draining compost mix, if repotting")

Plant.create(name: "Red Coral Cactus", 
img_url:"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0156/3996/9840/products/IMG_E5907.jpg?v=1605178891", 
info: "Care Information
Site
The best spot for this is an east facing window for fresh morning sun and protection from midday rays. A window can magnify the heat of sunlight and burn the leaves, so make sure it's not getting hit from above!

Temperature
It's quite sensitive to cold so is best kept above 15°C 

Water
Unlike many cacti, this plant loves a good drink during summer. When watering, make sure you soak the compost entirely and allow to dry out before watering again. During winter, water very sparingly to avoid root-rot.

Feeding
Cactus food during summer. Always follow manufacturer instructions.

Tip
Susceptible to mealybug. Check regularly for cotton-wool looking insects and wipe clean periodically. ")

Plant.create(name: "String of Beads", 
img_url:"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1000/4150/products/IMG_6570_grande.jpg?v=1603986839", 
info: "Care Information
Site
Bright, indirect light

Temperature
Maintain temperatures of above 10c

They are adapted to dry arid conditions, therefore no need to increase humidity in the room.

Water
Unlike other succulents, they do like water on a fairly frequent basis during the growing season. However, they will easily rot if over-watered or left to sit in water. 

Allow the soil to dry out between waterings.

Feeding
Diluted succulent or houseplant feed annually 

Tip
May not be ideal if you have young children or pets (particuarly cats) as the moving stems can be appealing to playful pets.")

Plant.create(name: "Pink Robusta", 
img_url:"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0031/6669/9629/products/IMG_8494_large.jpg?v=1598631042", 
info: "Care Information
Site
A nice bright spot with plenty of filtered light. The delicate leaves are easily scorched though, so avoid direct sunlight to keep that gorgeous rosy colour. 

Temperature
It originates in Africa, so it's used to a hotter climate. Try to keep it above 13 Celcius. 

Water
Allow the compost to dry out between waterings, then give it a good soaking and make sure the pot has plenty of drainage.

Feeding
A very weak liquid plant food once or twice a month during the growing season.

Tip
This plant is easy to propagate. Just take a cutting and make sure that 3 or 4 nodes are attached and place in water. You will have to wait at least 3 weeks before roots start appearing, so be patient!")

Plant.create(name: "Maiden's Blush", 
img_url:"data:image/jpeg;base64,", 
info: "
Care Information
Site
It absolutely loves bright spots out of direct sunlight. It will however, manage almost anywhere. Feel free to get it out in the garden during summer. 

Temperature
Do not let the average temperature drop below 10 Celcius. 

Water
Average watering. Allow the soil to dry out before giving it a big drink about once a week during hot spells, and about once a month during the winter period. 

Feeding
About once a month during the growing season with a diluted plant feed. Very sparingly in winter, if at all. 

Tip
It won't grow much higher than 30-40cm tall, so a great way to make a statement is to propagate it and install a living wall out of them!")

Plant.create(name: "Wandering jew", 
img_url:"https://images.saymedia-content.com/.image/t_share/MTc0ODI0NzY1NTQwODA0MzY3/how-to-grow-wandering-jew-spiderwort.jpg", 
info: "Care Information
Site
A bright position out of direct sunlight.

Temperature
This is a fairly robust plant liking average warmth, avoid drops below 10 - 12c.

Water
Keep well watered in summer and infrequently in winter. Mist leaves occasionally.

Feeding
A liquid feed every 3 weeks or so.

Tip
Easily propagates from stem cuttings any time apart from winter.")

